trong>Transportation (Optional)</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Lunch (Optional)</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>PTD Fee</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Medical fee</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Registration fee</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Development Levy</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Saturday lesson</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SCHOOL RULES</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><u>P.T.D:</u> This meeting holds in the school once every term at 3:30pm and by 4pm, the school gate is shut. Any parent that is absent will pay a fine as agreed on by the body. No delegate is permitted to attend the meeting apart from parents of the school.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Arrival time for the pupils:</u> Every child of the school must be in school (Monday &ndash; Friday), on or before 7:30 am. The school gate closes 7:30am. If there is any circumstance that will cause a child to be late to school, the parents of such a child must communicate before the above time so as to gain entrance on arrival.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Hair pattern:</u> The school has her simple hair style for girls, which is flat weaving with little or no beads. No other hair style is allowed for the girls.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Communication:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No parent of the school is permitted to have a teacher&rsquo;s number. Rather, if there is any communication to be made, it goes through the administrative office.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Open day:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The school observes a day in a term when parents of the school come to see their children&rsquo;s performance and interact with the teachers of their child / ward. Parents should be careful not to exchange phone numbers or gifts. Everything should be done through the Office.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Writing Materials/ Snacks:</u> The pupils of the school are not allowed to come to school with any writing material, snacks or object of any kind apart from their lunch &amp; water. The Nursery school pupils are allowed to come to school with their snacks or fruits not sweets or chewing gum.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Uniform pattern:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The school has a unique uniform for her pupils: the Polo of the day goes with Blue Jean, Jacket, White trainers &amp; White Stockings.</li>\r\n	<li>Red Polo {wt collar} &amp; red cap</li>\r\n	<li>: Green Polo, White &amp; Green cap</li>\r\n	<li>: White Polo &amp; Blue cap</li>\r\n	<li>: Same as Monday</li>\r\n	<li>: Same as Wednesday</li>\r\n	<li>Decent wears with shoe/sandals <u>NOT </u>Slippers, Bum shorts, sleeveless, tights, leggings or transparent wears.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Transportation system:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The children are expected to wait for the school bus in their various bus posts and not the drivers waiting. No parent is expected to give drivers message for the school management or call him/ her for an official message. It must be done through the administrative office.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Lesson:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Parents are not expected to contact any teacher for any form of private home lesson for their kids, as this is against the ethics of the school.</li>\r\n	<li>The school does not observe Public holidays except Children&rsquo;s Day and Independence Day, therefore any day your child will be absent from school, communicate through the Administrative office.</li>\r\n	<li>Any child of the school is free to celebrate his/ her birthday in the school. This comes up from Monday to Thursday. The gift items must get to the School before 12pm. Chocolates, Sweets, Chewing gum or cooked food are not allowed. Remember to communicate to the school earlier on the date.</li>\r\n	<li>The homework given to the kids is for them to handle it themselves. Parents/ Guardians are not permitted to write their children&rsquo;s homework.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>NB: Visiting Day is every last Saturday of the month. Time: 9am &ndash; 5pm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No student comes in with any c